d cs/ip ss/sp in sigcontext with its own.<br />&gt;   But __pad0 still has DOS SS, which crash because (presumably)<br />&gt;   the DOS LDT have been just removed"<br /><br />Side note: if this is the main issue, and the problem is the "iret"<br />faulting when trying to restore SS (and causing an unexpected SIGSEGV<br />that dosemu crashes on), then an alternate model might be to keep the<br />save/restore SS code, but do a "VERW" on the SS descriptor in<br />restore_sigcontext(), and silently just replacing it with __USER_DS if<br />that fails.<br /><br />                       Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
